<p><a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://researchforum.microsoft.com/?OCID=msr_researchforum_MCR_Blog_Promo" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Microsoft 研究论坛<span class="sr-only">（在新选项卡中打开）</span></a>是一系列新的对话，探讨全球研究界的最新进展、大胆的新想法和重要讨论。领先的微软研究人员将分享他们的工作见解，然后与观众进行现场在线讨论。</p><p>这篇文章概述了首届微软研究论坛对话，并对每个演讲进行了总结。完整的详细信息，包括<a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://msrchat.azurewebsites.net/">副驾驶体验<span class="sr-only">（在新选项卡中打开）</span></a>和<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/?OCID=msr_researchforum_MCR_Blog_Promo" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">每个会话的重播<span class="sr-only">（在新选项卡中打开）</span></a> ，均可按需提供。 <a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://register.researchforum.microsoft.com/?OCID=msr_researchforum_MCR_Blog_Promo" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">立即注册<span class="sr-only">（在新选项卡中打开）</span></a>以参加即将举行的研究论坛活动。</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="keynote-research-in-the-era-of-ai"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/keynote-research-in-the-era-of-ai/">主题演讲：人工智能时代的研究</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/keynote-research-in-the-era-of-ai/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720.jpg" alt="研究论坛 2024 年 1 月 - Peter Lee" class="wp-image-1002807" style="width:650px" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-343x193.jpg 343w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Peter-Keynote_1280x720-960x540.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></a></figure><p> <em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/petelee/">Peter Lee</a> ，微软研究院与孵化器首席副总裁</em></p><p>2023 年对于人工智能研究来说是令人难以置信的一年，变化迅速，通用人工智能的火花不断涌现。生成式人工智能现在影响着研究中的一切，而研究对于造福社会的创新技术来说从未如此重要。尽管有充足的理由保持乐观，但我们也必须清醒地认识到风险和局限性——这是研究可以发挥重要作用的另一个方向。</p><p>在这种环境下，开放和协作至关重要，不仅是为了推进研究，而且是为了确保技术开发时承诺安全和合乎道德的使用。 Microsoft 继续投资于其对负责任的 AI (RAI) 的承诺，它不仅深入集成到公司的每个工程团队中，而且还集成到财务、安全和法律团队等职能部门中。进一步的进展需要与更广泛的研究界密切合作。</p><p>一些最有前途和最切实的进步正在医学和材料科学领域出现。例子包括微软研究实验室<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/lab/microsoft-research-ai4science/">Microsoft AI4Science</a>的工作，该实验室正在与<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/ghddi-and-microsoft-research-use-ai-technology-to-achieve-significant-progress-in-discovering-new-drugs-to-treat-global-infectious-diseases/">全球健康药物发现研究所</a>合作，加速发现传染病新疗法。</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="panel-discussion-ai-frontiers"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/lab/ai-frontiers/articles/panel-discussion-ai-frontiers">小组讨论：人工智能前沿</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/lab/ai-frontiers/articles/panel-discussion-ai-frontiers/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720.jpg" alt="研究论坛 2024 年 1 月 - 与 Ashley Llorens、Sebastien Bubeck、Ahmed Awadallah 和 Ece Kamar 进行小组讨论" class="wp-image-1002804" style="width:650px" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-343x193.jpg 343w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Panel-discussion_1280x720-960x540.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></a></figure><p> <em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/allorens/">Ashley Llorens</a> ，微软副总裁兼杰出科学家<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/eckamar/">Ece Kamar</a> ，微软人工智能前沿研究院董事总经理<br><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/sebubeck/">Sébastien Bubeck</a> ，微软 GenAI 副总裁</em><br><em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/hassanam/">Ahmed Awadallah</a> ，微软人工智能前沿研究院高级首席研究经理</em></p><p>小组成员探讨了他们在不久的将来对人工智能的期望，以及需要克服的挑战。示例包括：</p><ul><li>超越语言来构建人工智能系统，成为物理世界的帮手。人工智能可以做的不仅仅是回答问题；它可以更好地理解我们的目标和意图，并改变人们的生活。</li><li>除了试图让人工智能模仿人类思维之外，人工智能能否真正<em>阐明</em>人类思维的工作原理并揭示推理的基础？</li><li>让人工智能技术变得更小将有助于降低成本并提高当前人工智能系统的性能。我们如何将问题分成更小的部分来解决？如何降低对大数据、大神经网络、海量计算资源的要求？</li><li>我们能否创建一个良性反馈循环，让人工智能向使用它的人学习，而不是简单地从静态信息库中提供答案？</li></ul><p>小组成员还探讨了技术的快速发展。三到五年的历史时间表现在被压缩为短短几周。在这种环境下，协作对于跨组织快速开发想法和扩大实验至关重要。这也加剧了人们对优化安全性和减轻语言模型偏见的现有担忧。</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="lightning-talks">闪电演讲</h2><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="improving-reasoning-in-language-models-with-laser-layer-selective-rank-reduction"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/improving-reasoning-in-language-models-with-laser-layer-selective-rank-reduction">使用 LASER 改进语言模型的推理：层选择性降级</a></h3><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/improving-reasoning-in-language-models-with-laser-layer-selective-rank-reduction/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720.jpg" alt="研究论坛 2024 年 1 月 - Dipendra Misra" class="wp-image-1002795" style="width:650px" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-343x193.jpg 343w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Dipendra-Lightning1_1280x720-960x540.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></a></figure><p> <em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/dimisra/">Dipendra Misra</a> ，微软纽约研究院和 AI Frontiers 高级研究员</em></p><p>大型语言模型 (LLM) 彻底改变了机器学习。随着研究人员不断推进这项技术，一种方法是对模型进行干预并观察这如何影响其性能。本演讲介绍了 LASER，这是一种新的干预方法，可以提高法学硕士的准确性，同时减少其内存占用。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="evaluation-and-understanding-of-foundation-models"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/evaluation-and-understanding-of-foundation-models/">基础模型的评估和理解</a></h3><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/evaluation-and-understanding-of-foundation-models/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720.jpg" alt="研究论坛 2024 年 1 月 - Besmira Nushi" class="wp-image-1002792" style="width:650px" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-343x193.jpg 343w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Besmira-Lightning2_1280x720-960x540.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></a></figure><p> <em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/benushi/">Besmira Nushi</a> ，微软人工智能前沿研究院首席研究员</em></p><p>模型评估和理解是人工智能创新的指南。但评估是困难的，新的生成任务对评估和理解提出了新的挑战。本次演讲探讨了衡量、告知和加速模型改进的努力，这有助于科学界理解和研究新形式和水平的智力。 </p><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="generative-ai-meets-structural-biology-equilibrium-distribution-prediction"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/generative-ai-meets-structural-biology-equilibrium-distribution-prediction/">生成式人工智能与结构生物学的结合：平衡分布预测</a></h3><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/generative-ai-meets-structural-biology-equilibrium-distribution-prediction/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720.jpg" alt="研究论坛 2024 年 1 月 - Shuxin Cheng" class="wp-image-1002816" style="width:650px" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-343x193.jpg 343w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Shuxin-Lightning4_1280x720-960x540.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></a></figure><p><em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/shuz/">郑树新</a>，微软研究院AI4Science首席研究员</em></p><p>分布式图形分析器 (DIG) 是一种深度学习框架，用于更准确地预测蛋白质结构，这是分子科学中的一项基本挑战。 DIG 使用生成式 AI 来解决预测均衡分布的问题，开启了令人兴奋的新可能性。通过了解分子的不同状态和行为，科学家可以在开发新药、创造先进材料和理解生物过程方面取得突破。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="augmenting-human-cognition-and-decision-making-with-ai"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/augmenting-human-cognition-and-decision-making-with-ai/">利用人工智能增强人类认知和决策</a></h3><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/augmenting-human-cognition-and-decision-making-with-ai/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720.jpg" alt="研究论坛 2024 年 1 月 - Jake Hofman" class="wp-image-1002801" style="width:650px" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-343x193.jpg 343w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Jake-Lightning3_1280x720-960x540.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></a></figure><p> <em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/jmh/">Jake Hofman</a> ，微软纽约研究院高级首席研究员</em></p><p>人工智能如何帮助人们做出更好的决策、提高工作效率并以可持续的方式提高自我？有些技术可以在短期内提供帮助，但无法提供持久的解决方案。例如，依赖拼写检查器可能不会提高一个人正确拼写的能力。本次演讲探讨了人工智能工具的设计和使用中的选择，以帮助做出决策，以及严格测量和实验以最大化收益和最小化风险的重要性。</p><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="kahani-visual-storytelling-through-culturally-nuanced-images"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/kahani-visual-storytelling-through-culturally-nuanced-images/">Kahani：通过文化上细致入微的图像来讲述视觉故事</a></h3><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/kahani-visual-storytelling-through-culturally-nuanced-images/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720.jpg" alt="研究论坛 2024 年 1 月 - Sameer Segal" class="wp-image-1002813" style="width:650px" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-343x193.jpg 343w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Sameer-Lightning5_1280x720-960x540.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></a></figure><p> <em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/sameersegal/">Sameer Segal</a> ，微软印度研究院首席研究软件开发工程师</em></p><p>图像生成模型可以根据自然语言描述生成视觉上令人惊叹的图像，但它们通常缺乏文化意识和细微差别。这些模型可能依赖于刻板印象，无法理解本地单词，这需要大量修复，例如修改或显着微调模型。图像生成还需要复杂的提示，这超出了许多外行的能力。</p><p>本次演讲着眼于 Kahani，这是一个微软研究项目，专注于开发视觉叙事原型，让人们只需用当地语言描述图像即可创建视觉上引人注目且文化上微妙的图像。 Kahani 利用修复等最先进的技术以及 Segment Anything 和 GPT-4V(ision) 等模型来生成候选图像的反馈。</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="closing-remarks-and-announcements"> <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/research-forum-closing-remarks-and-announcements/">结束语和公告</a></h2><figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/quarterly-brief/jan-2024-brief/articles/research-forum-closing-remarks-and-announcements/"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720.jpg" alt="研究论坛 2024 年 1 月 - Ashley Llorens" class="wp-image-1002714" style="width:650px" srcset="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720.jpg 1280w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-300x169.jpg 300w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-768x432.jpg 768w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-1066x600.jpg 1066w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-655x368.jpg 655w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-343x193.jpg 343w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-240x135.jpg 240w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-640x360.jpg 640w, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/uploads/prod/2024/01/RF-2024Jan_Ashley_Close_1280x720-960x540.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></a></figure><p> <em><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/allorens/">Ashley Llorens</a> ，微软副总裁兼杰出科学家</em></p><p>人工智能的加速发展凸显了跨学科、组织和地域参与的重要性。本次会议介绍了<a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://aka.ms/MSRAISocietyFellow">微软研究院人工智能与社会研究员<span class="sr-only">（在新选项卡中打开）</span></a>计划的第一批研究员，该计划旨在促进深入的跨学科合作，最大限度地发挥人工智能对人类和社会的价值。会议还介绍了<a class="msr-external-link glyph-append glyph-append-open-in-new-tab glyph-append-xsmall" href="https://aka.ms/afmr">加速基础模型研究<span class="sr-only">（在新选项卡中打开）</span></a> (AFMR) 计划的最新情况，该计划发放赠款，使通过 Microsoft Azure 托管的领先模型可供学术研究团队使用。迄今为止，AFMR 赠款正在支持全球 80 个研究机构的近 200 个项目。这些项目包括人工智能模型创新和评估、负责任的人工智能、健康、人工智能科学发现等领域的工作。</p><span id="label-external-link" class="sr-only" aria-hidden="true">在新选项卡中打开</span><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/microsoft-research-forum-new-series-explores-bold-ideas-in-technology-research-in-the-era-of-ai/">微软研究院论坛：探索人工智能时代技术研究的大胆想法的新系列文章</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research">微软研究院</a>。</p> ;
